# Security headers for the Fizz static site (Netlify). The /bridge page brokers
# wallet connections + L1 approvals, so clickjacking and a missing CSP are real
# risks. These are committed (zero-build); deploy-to-landing.mjs only touches
# bridge/ launch/ webassets/, so this file survives rebuilds.
#
# CSP is ENFORCING. connect-src is pinned to exactly what the pages need: the
# Aztec mainnet node (read addresses), a public Ethereum-mainnet RPC (L1 reads +
# deposit simulate/receipt), and WalletConnect's relay/telemetry (only used if
# the user picks the WalletConnect connector; injected wallets route through
# window.ethereum and need no connect-src entry). 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is required
# — claim-secret generation compiles poseidon2 via WebAssembly; worker-src
# allows the same-origin module workers (blob: is a bb.js fallback); data: in
# connect-src is the inlined gzipped wasm bb.js fetch-decodes. If a wallet
# connector breaks, temporarily switch the directive name to
# Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only and widen from the violation reports.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'none'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'none'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; worker-src 'self' blob:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' data: https://aztec-mainnet.drpc.org https://ethereum-rpc.publicnode.com https://*.walletconnect.org https://*.walletconnect.com wss://relay.walletconnect.org; frame-src https://verify.walletconnect.org https://verify.walletconnect.com
